# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your actual values for local development.

## Gemini API Configuration
```
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
```

Get your Gemini API key from: https://ai.google.dev

## Firebase Configuration (Optional for local development)

For local development, you can skip Firebase setup. However, for production deployment on Netlify, these must be configured in your Netlify site settings (not in this file).

```
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_FIRESTORE_DATABASE_ID=
```

### Obtaining Firebase Credentials

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Select your project
3. Click the gear icon → Project Settings
4. Navigate to the "Service Accounts" tab
5. Copy your Firebase config values

### Setting up Netlify Environment Variables

1. Go to your Netlify site dashboard
2. Navigate to **Site Settings > Build & Deploy > Environment**
3. Click "Edit variables"
4. Add each `VITE_FIREBASE_*` variable with the corresponding value
5. Deploy to apply changes

---

**IMPORTANT:** Never commit this file with actual credentials. The `.env.local` file is ignored by git for security.
